===Etymology===
From {{Skr.}} [[अवतारः]] (avatāraḥ) via Hindustani [[अवतार]] / {{URchar|[[اوتار]]}} (avatār), meaning "descent (of a [[deity]] from [[heaven]] in [[incarnate]] form)", from ''avatāriti'' "he descends": ''ava-'' "down" and ''tariti'' "(he) crosses".

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The physical [[embodiment]] of an [[idea]] or [[concept]]; a [[personification]].
# {{computing}} A [[digital]] [[representation]] of a [[person]] or [[being]].
# {{context|hinduism}} The earthly [[incarnation]] of a deity, particularly [[Vishnu]].

